The paper presents an exact algorithm for solving 1-in-3 SAT, which is a variant of 3-SAT. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with algorithms and complexity theory, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper involves solving a combinatorial problem, it could also belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with discrete mathematics and combinatorics, such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
